description:

Our favor ribbon is designed for wrapping, attaching favor tags, and personalizing your wedding cake, party favors and gifts.   Printing can appear on each end of the ribbon with the middle left blank for tying or you may opt for continuous printing.  A popular way to personalize your wedding favors is to print your names on one end and the wedding date (event date) on the other.

We use satin ribbon in 3/8 inch widths or 5/8 inch widths.  

Ribbon Colors - antique white, aqua, black, burgundy, chocolate, hot pink, hunter green, kiwi, light blue, light orchid, light pink, lemon yellow, navy, orange, pewter, purple, red, royal blue, silver, white.

description:
For a simple design with a modern flair, check out our modern circles Save the Date Cards.  

Design 1 (blue circles & green border)

A strip of a geometric design was added to the bottom of a White A7 card. At the top of the card, we added the future bride and groom’s names in green using the Alyssa Afternoon font. We joined the names with a blue ampersand without any spaces. The wedding details have been added in blue,  the words “Invitation to follow” are in a blue font, and the geometric design runs all the way to the edge of the card. We lined the Midnight envelopes in Clover and added coordinating Personalized Envelope Liners with the couple’s names and the wedding date. (Personalized Envelope Liners and Metallic A8 Portrait Pocket Folders with no flap are sold separately).

Design 2 (green circles & blue border)

For a bold, modern look, try our modern circles (green & blue) A7 Invitation.  We added a border to a White A7 flat card and used a floating text box to add the bride and groom’s first names and the wedding date in the center of the border. We wrote the bride and groom’s names in green using the Trebuchet font and joined the names using a blue ampersand. Below the border, we added the bride and groom’s full names in green and the wedding details in blue using the Trebuchet font. We lined the Midnight envelopes using our new modern circles (green & blue) Personalized Envelope Liners with the couple’s initials and wedding date.


There invitation includes an A7 card and white A8 envelope. Invitations are printed on 120 lb smooth natural cotton card stock.  Envelopes made  with 70 lb paper.

Personalized Envelope Liners ($0.87 ea), matte or metallic envelopes colored (additional $0.15 ea),  and A8 Metallic Portrait Pocket Folders ($2.75 ea)  sold separately.
